@startuml Demo Load Report
title Demo Flow: Load Report to Editor

actor "Demo User" as User
participant "AlpineJS (Frontend)" as UI
participant "ReportBuilderController" as Controller
participant "SavedReport (Model)" as DBReport

User -> UI : Click "📚 Saved Reports Library"
activate UI
UI -> Controller : GET /builder/saved
activate Controller
Controller --> UI : JSON Array of Saved Reports
deactivate Controller
UI -> UI : Render List
UI --> User : Display Modal
deactivate UI

User -> UI : Click "Load" on a Report
activate UI
UI -> Controller : GET /builder/saved/{id}/load
activate Controller

Controller -> DBReport : findOrFail(id)
activate DBReport
DBReport --> Controller : SavedReport Model
deactivate DBReport

Controller -> Controller : Parse payload (decode JSON string)
Controller --> UI : JSON Response\n{success: true, payload: AST}
deactivate Controller

UI -> UI : Map AST to Flat UI Payload\n(Flatten Filters, flatten Attributes)
note left of UI: Critical step: Translates strictly-typed\nBackend AST back to AlpineJS state.

UI -> UI : Trigger reactivity (Update visual blocks)
UI --> User : Display Populated Builder Blocks
deactivate UI

@enduml
